        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(embedded-runner): keep active compaction retries from looking stuck",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Problem: long-running embedded runs could be misclassified as stuck while compaction retry work was still actively in flight.\n- Why it matters: stuck-session recovery could treat active work as invalid or stalled work, which risks incorrect cleanup behavior for long-running tasks.\n- What changed: diagnostic session progress is refreshed before long embedded prompt work and while compaction retries remain active, and regression tests were added to lock in the retry heartbeat path and observe-only stuck recovery behavior.\n- What did NOT change (scope boundary): this PR does not change stuck-session recovery policy, abort thresholds, cleanup strategy outside this path, or any integration/channel-specific behavior.\n\n## Real behavior proof\nBehavior addressed: Active compaction retry waits should keep refreshing diagnostic session activity so long-running embedded work is preserved instead of being misclassified as stuck when active abort recovery remains disabled.\nReal environment tested: Real OpenClaw setup on device 25 (Ubuntu), source-built checkout at /home/ghost/src/openclaw-ghost, branch fix/stuck-task-heartbeat-upstream.\nExact steps or command run after this patch: On device 25, in /home/ghost/src/openclaw-ghost, run pnpm test src/agents/pi-embedded-runner/run/compaction-retry-aggregate-timeout.test.ts src/logging/diagnostic-stuck-session-recovery.runtime.test.ts, then inspect the live terminal output from that run and confirm both regression tests pass after the fix.\nEvidence after fix: Terminal output captured from the real device 25 run after the fix.\n```text\n[test] starting test/vitest/vitest.logging.config.ts\nPASS logging src/logging/diagnostic-stuck-session-recovery.runtime.test.ts (11 tests)\n[test] starting test/vitest/vitest.agents.config.ts\nPASS agents src/agents/pi-embedded-runner/run/compaction-retry-aggregate-timeout.test.ts (7 tests)\n[test] passed 2 Vitest shards in 24.86s\n```\nObserved result after fix: The real device 25 run completed successfully; the logging regression test passed with 11 tests, the aggregate-timeout regression test passed with 7 tests, and the Vitest shard run finished in 24.86 seconds.\nWhat was not tested: I did not run a full end-to-end synthetic harness covering every stuck-session recovery mode.",
